By: The Speaker and Delegate Bhandari and Delegates Bhandari, Alston, Bagnall,
Cullison, Guzzone, Hill, Hutchinson, S. Johnson, Kaufman, Kipke, Lopez,
Martinez, Rosenberg, Ross, Taveras, White Holland, and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Health
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 3, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Emergency Room Services and Post–Acute Care – Coverage and Facility Studies
3 FOR the purpose of prohibiting certain policies and contracts issued by insurers, nonprofit
4 health service plans, and health maintenance organizations from denying insurance
5 coverage for certain emergency room services under certain circumstances
6 authorizing the Maryland Insurance Commissioner to conduct an examination of
7 certain decisions by carriers related to claims or authorization requests for services
8 in, or related to services in, emergency departments; authorizing the Commissioner
9 to have certain decisions independently reviewed under certain circumstances;
10 requiring that a certain report required to be compiled by the Maryland Insurance
11 Commissioner include data on certain adverse decisions and grievances; requiring
12 the Maryland Health Care Commission, in conjunction with the Health Services Cost
13 Review Commission, to conduct a study to quantify bed capacity in hospitals and
14 post–acute settings in the State and make a recommendation on a certain collection
15 and auditing process; requiring the Maryland Health Care Commission, in
16 consultation with the Health Services Cost Review Commission, to study analyzing
17 options to facilitate clinically appropriate transitions from acute to post–acute care
18 settings in the State; and generally relating to emergency room services and
19 post–acute care.
20 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
21 Article – Insurance
22 Section 15–1A–14
